statements: SELECT * FROM 3d_printing_designs;
SELECT design_name, designer_name FROM 3d_printing_designs WHERE material_used = 'PLA';

SELECT design_id, designer_name, material_used FROM 3d_printing_designs ORDER BY designer_name ASC;
SELECT * FROM 3d_printing_designs WHERE design_name LIKE '%model%' OR material_used='ABS';
SELECT designer_name, design_name, material_used FROM 3d_printing_designs WHERE material_used='PLA' ORDER BY design_name DESC;
SELECT * FROM designs;
SELECT design_name, designer_name FROM designs;
SELECT design_name, design_file_url FROM designs WHERE designer_name = 'Alice';

SELECT design_name, COUNT(design_id) AS design_count FROM designs GROUP BY designer_name HAVING COUNT(design_id) > 1;

SELECT * FROM designs;
SELECT design_name, design_file FROM designs;
SELECT spec_name, dimensions FROM specifications;

SELECT spec_name, material FROM specifications WHERE material = 'Plastic' ORDER BY spec_name ASC;

SELECT design_name, printer_name, bed_size FROM designs d JOIN printers p ON d.design_id = p.printer_id WHERE design_name LIKE '%table%' ORDER BY bed_size ASC, printer_name DESC;

SELECT id, build_volume FROM printers ORDER BY id ASC;

SELECT id, name FROM designs WHERE name LIKE '%example%' AND file_path LIKE '/path/to/file%';
SELECT u.username, d.name, s.material, s.layer_thickness FROM users u JOIN designs d ON u.id = d.id JOIN specifications s ON d.id = s.design_id WHERE u.username = 'john_doe';
SELECT p.manufacturer, COUNT(*) AS total_printer_count FROM printers p JOIN specifications s ON p.name = s.material GROUP BY p.manufacturer;

SELECT d.name AS design_name, p.brand AS printer_brand, pj.start_time AS print_start FROM Design d INNER JOIN PrintJob pj ON d.id = pj.design_id INNER JOIN Printer p ON pj.printer_id = p.id;
